<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910301-0074</DOCNO><DOCID>910301-0074.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Fund American Cos.:   Firm Planning to Buy Back   As Much as 30% of Shares</HL><DATE>03/01/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C22</SO><CO>   FFC</CO><IN>INSURANCE (INS)PROPERTY andamp; CASUALTY INSURANCE (INP)BUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, SWAP OFFERS (BBK)</IN><LP>   Fund American Cos. said its board authorized therepurchase of as many as 6.6 million shares, or 30% of itscommon stock outstanding, as part of the company'sliquidation plan.   The company -- which completed the sale of its principalsubsidiary, Fireman's Fund Insurance Co., last January -- isslated to complete its liquidation Jan. 2, 1996, under a planapproved in December. The repurchased shares, to be acquiredfrom time to time in the open market or in privatetransactions, will be retired, the company said in Purchase,N.Y.</LP><TEXT>   The authorization follows the purchase of 9.1 millionshares in February under a tender offer. The company hasn'tdisclosed its cash position but public documents indicatethat it has around $275 million.   Fund American shares closed yesterday at $61, up $2.375,in New York Stock Exchange composite trading.</TEXT></DOC>